    "body": "> I'm not sure I'm buying what you're selling here, [@domenkozar](https://github.com/domenkozar). starship has a Node.js module and a Bun module. They're both JavaScript runtimes.\n> \n> When I enter a project that has a `flake.nix` I want starship to let me know about that, so that I don't even need to list the files to know that I can run `nix develop`. And if a project has a `devenv.nix` file, then I'd like starship to inform me of that, so that I don't have to list the files to know that I can run `devenv shell`.\n\nMaybe starship needs to tell you flavor of Nix, being plain Nix (default.nix), flakes (flake.nix) or devenv (devenv.nix)",
